Add ``Perl(float_format=Perl.float_formats.MATH_BIG_FLOAT)`` to wrap every float as ``Math::BigFloat->new("...")`` (with a ``use Math::BigFloat;`` preamble) so downstream encoders such as ``JSON::PP`` and ``JSON::XS`` in ``allow_bignum`` mode round-trip the full ``repr`` precision instead of silently applying their 15-digit ``%.15g`` default, which previously rounded ``DBL_MAX`` up past its representable range and decoded back as ``inf``.
